name: Fallon & Byrne
addresses: 24-28 Swan Centre Castlewood Avenue, Rathmines, Dublin 6
The People’s Park, Park Road, Dún Laoghaire, Co. Dublin
information:
There’s a simple idea behind Fallon & Byrne, and it’s this. We believe in wonderful food, fine wine, great company. We put it on our food hall shelves and in our counters for you to take away. Or we serve it to you, in any of several ways in any of our restaurants. We’ll even bring the whole experience to you to cater for an event at home or in work. In short, the answer is yes. Now what’s the question?

Three unique locations. One unique experience. 

Over 12 years, Fallon & Byrne has established itself as Dublin’s foodie mecca, and THE place to consummate your love of all things delicious.

name: Joe's
addresses: Arnotts Department Store Life Street, D1
information:
In short, we are proud to be one of the 80 best coffee shops across the globe that The Barn works with. We are proud to be part of THE BARN FAMILY. 

We've invested in training and learning for our company as we hope that will continually enhance what we're trying to do. We use their incredible knowledge to get the best out of each cup. 

But most importantly, we believe that great coffee is a luxury that everyone should be able to enjoy.

Domini & Peaches Kemp

Directors and Co-founders of Joe's

name: Clement and Pekoe
information: We are a neighbourhood cafe based on bustling South William Street. Tea and Coffee is what we are about, and we mean the proper stuff. We are passionate about high-grade Loose Leaf Tea and the best Coffee we can get our hands on. We brew it, sell it, talk about it, consume it and are consumed by it. Our name is dedicated to our love of both.

menu.name: Lemon Caiprianhi Green Tea

name: Proper Order Coffee Co.
information: Opening our doors in January 2016, Proper Order fast became a destination coffee shop for the people of Dublin and even International visitors. With an emphasis on brewing coffee from some of the best coffee roasters in the world we've grown from a team of just two to now include a training school with an exciting new location on the way in 2018.

name: Love Supreme
information: OUR LOVELY COFFEE IS ROASTED BY THE MIGHTY CHARLIE AND ANNE OF KOPPI FINE COFFEE ROASTERS

menu.name: HILE KAPU COFFEE SCOOP & BAG CLIP

name: Cloud Cafe
information: We are a neighbourhood cafe located on the North Strand Road. Cloud Café was created in 2011 with a focus on catering events with healthy and nutritious dishes. Having worked in the restaurant and food industry for over two decades, the dream of opening up our own place was stronger than ever and in 2016 we got the opportunity to open the Cloud Cafe store.

name: Network Cafe
information: Network is an exciting new coffee shop open seven days a week on Aungier Street, it will serve high quality coffee in a relaxed and friendly environment.

name: Coffee Angel
information: Coffee Angel have expanded to three set locations across the city but still manage to keep a real local feel in all of their cafes. The staff are always friendly and the coffee is hot and fresh – the perfect combination.

name: Shoe Lane Coffee
information: Step back to the 1800’s and the vintage Singer machines and traditional shoe making materials in the window of our busy little coffee shop would have been making shoes on the same spot. The sewing machines and wooden lasts in the window were donated by the nearby Tara Leather, the last of a row of cobblers that made up ‘Shoe Lane’, now known as Tara St.

name: Kaph
information: A minimally-hip coffeehouse serving 3fe coffee blends and tasty paleo-friendly snacks, Kaph is a calming retreat away from busy Grafton area, and a perfect place to get some work done on your laptop for an hour or so. Try their coconut-soy flat white and have your life changed forever.
